<subSubSection id="C301F0D2FFBDFF92A3A9FA0EFD5062B5" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA4A359FFBDFF92A3A9FA0EFD5062B5" blockId="14.[151,1437,1230,1509]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">
<emphasis id="B96F7F4BFFBDFF92A3A9FA0EFE9C62CD" bold="true" box="[151,256,1411,1437]" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">Remark.</emphasis>
The genitalia in this species group are poor in significant characters; molecular evidence is needed. More specimens must be collected and the DNA must be squenced to be sure about the identification. Thus, we have decided to treat this taxon as 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BD8DAFFBDFF92A132FA46FD5B62B5" authorityName="Delgado &amp; Jach" authorityYear="2007" box="[524,711,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Ochthebius" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="judemaesi">
<emphasis id="B96F7F4BFFBDFF92A132FA46FDB462B5" box="[524,552,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">O.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B96F7F4BFFBDFF92A16CFA46FD5B62B5" box="[594,711,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">judemaesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96F7F4BFFBDFF92A1F6FA46FD5062B5" box="[712,716,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="465">.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
